ours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|Tanzania}}: Honorary Citizen of [[Dar es Salaam]] (2005)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United Kingdom}}: The Gold Mercury International \"AD PERSONAM\" Award (1982)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United Kingdom}}: Honorary Fellowship, [[Royal Institute of British Architects]] (1991)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United Kingdom}}: Andrew Carnegie Medal of Philanthropy (2005)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United Kingdom}}: Winner of the 10th annual [[Peter O'Sullevan]] Award at the Savoy in London (2006)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: [[Thomas Jefferson Memorial]] Foundation Medal in Architecture, [[University of Virginia]] (1984)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: Institute Honor of the [[American Institute of Architects]] (1984)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: Honorary Member of the [[American Institute of Architects]] (1992)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: Foreign Honorary Member of the [[American Academy of Arts and Sciences]] (1996)<ref name=AAAS>{{cite web|title=Book of Members, 1780\u20132010: Chapter A|url=http://www.amacad.org/publications/BookofMembers/ChapterA.pdf|publisher=American Academy of Arts and Sciences|accessdate=6 April 2011| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110510021801/http://www.amacad.org/publications/BookofMembers/ChapterA.pdf| archivedate=10 May 2011 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: Hadrian Award, [[World Monuments Fund]] (1996)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: [[Vincent Scully Prize]], [[National Building Museum]] (2005)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: Key to the City of [[Austin]] (2008)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: Key to the City of [[Sugar Land, Texas]] (2018)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|United States}}: ULI [[J.C. Nichols]] Prize for Visionaries in [[Urban Development]], Los Angeles (2011)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n* {{Flagu|Uzbekistan}}: Honorary Citizen of the City of [[Samarkand]] and presented with a key to the city of [[Samarkand]] (1992)<ref name=\"List of honours\"/>\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{more citations needed|section|date=October 2017}}\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n|1= 1. '''Aga Khan IV'''\n|2= 2. [[Prince Aly Khan]]\n|3= 3. Joan Barbara Yarde-Buller\n|4= 4. [[Aga Khan III]]\n|5= 5. Cleope Teresa Magliano\n|6= 6. [[John Yarde-Buller, 3rd Baron Churston]]\n|7= 7. [[Denise Orme|Jessie Smither]]\n|8= 8. [[Aga Khan II]]\n|9= 9. Shams al-Muluk\n|12= 12. [[John Yarde-Buller, 2nd Baron Churston]]\n|13= 13. Barbara Yelverton\n|14= 14. Alfred John Smither\n|15= 15. Jessica Henrietta Pococke\n|16= 16. [[Aga Khan I]]\n|17= 17. Sarv-i Jahan Khanum\n|18= 18. [[Mirza]] Ali Muhammad Nizam al-Dawla\n|19= 19. Khurshid Kulah Khanum\n|24= 24. John Yarde-Buller\n|25= 25. Charlotte Pole\n|26= 26. [[Hastings Yelverton|Sir Hastings Reginald Yelverton]]\n|27= 27. [[Barbara Rawdon-Hastings, Marchioness of Hastings|Barbara Rawdon-Hastings, 20th Baroness Grey of Ruthyn]]\n}}\n\n===Patrilineal descent===\n\n{{chart top|text-align=left|Patrilineal descent<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ismailignosis.com/2016/07/09/the-aga-khans-direct-descent-from-prophet-muhammad-historical-proof/ |title=The Aga Khan's Direct Descent from Prophet Muhammad: Historical Proof |website=[[Ismail Gnosis]] |archivedate=9 July 2016 |accessdate=8 October 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref>}}\nShah Karim al-Hussaini Aga Khan's patriline is the line from which he is descended father to son.\n\n;Nizari Imams of the Fatimid Dynasty\n#[[Adnan]]\n#[[Ma'ad ibn Adnan]]\n#Nizar ibn Ma'ad\n#Mudar ibn Nizar\n#Ilyas ibn Mudar\n#[[Mudrikah ibn Ilyas]]\n#Khuzayma ibn Mudrika\n#Kinanah ibn Khuzayma\n#[[An-Nadr ibn Kinanah]]\n#Malik ibn Al-Nadr\n#[[Fihr ibn Malik]]\n#Ghalib ibn Fihr\n#[[Lu'ayy ibn Ghalib]]\n#[[Ka'b ibn Lu'ayy]]\n#[[Murrah ibn Ka'b]]\n#[[Kilab ibn Murrah]] b. ca. 372\n#[[Qusay ibn Kilab]] ca. 400-ca. 480\n#[[Abd Manaf ibn Qusai]]\n#[[Hashim ibn Abd Manaf]], ca. 464-ca. 497\n#[[Abd al-Muttalib]], ca. 497\u2013578\n#[[Abu Talib ibn Abd al-Muttalib]], 535\u2013619\n#Imam [[Ali ibn Abu Talib]], 601\u2013661\n#Imam [[Husayn ibn Ali]], 626\u2013680\n#Imam [[Ali ibn Husayn Zayn al-Abidin]], 659\u2013713\n#Imam [[Muhammad al-Baqir]], 677\u2013733\n#Imam [[Jafar al-Sadiq]], ca. 702\u2013765\n#Imam [[Ismail ibn Jafar]], ca. 722-ca. 762\n#Imam [[Muhammad ibn Ismail]], 740\u2013813\n#Imam [[Ahmad al-Wafi]], 795/746-827/828\n#Imam [[Muhammad at-Taqi (Isma'ili)]], 813/814-839/840\n#Imam [[Radi Abdullah]], 832\u2013881\n#Caliph [[Abdullah al-Mahdi Billah]], 873\u2013934\n#Caliph [[Al-Qa'im (Fatimid caliph)|Al-Qa'im]], 893\u2013946\n#Caliph [[Al-Mansur Billah]], 914\u2013953\n#Caliph [[Al-Mu'izz li-Din Allah]], 932\u2013975\n#Caliph [[Al-Aziz Billah]], 955\u2013996\n#Caliph [[Al-Hakim bi-Amr Allah]], 985\u20131021\n#Calpih [[Ali az-Zahir]], 1005\u20131036\n#Caliph [[Al-Mustansir Billah]], 1029\u20131094\n#Imam [[Nizar al-Mustafa]], 1047\u20131097\n#Imam Ali Al-Husayn Al-Hadi \n#Imam Al-Mutadi, Muhammad I, 1106\u20131157\n#Imam Al-Qahir, Hasan I, 1126\u20131162\n#Imam [[Hassan II of Alamut]], 1142/1145-1166 \n#Imam [[Muhammad II of Alamut]], 1148\u20131210\n#Imam [[Hassan III of Alamut]], 1187\u20131221\n#Imam [[Muhammad III of Alamut]], 1211\u20131255\n#Imam [[Rukn al-Din Khurshah]], ca. 1230-1256/1257\n#Imam [[Shams al-Din (Nizari)]], 1257\u20131310\n#Imam Qasim Shah\n#Imam Islam Shah, d. 1424\n#Imam Muhammad, d. 1464\n#Imam Ali Shah Qalandar, al-Mustansir Billah II, d. 1480\n#Imam Abd al-Salam Shah, d. 1494\n#Imam Abbas Shah Gharib, al-Mustansir Billah III, d. 1498\n#Imam Abuzar Ali Nur Shah, d. ca. 1509\n#Imam [[Mur\u0101d M\u012brz\u0101]], d. 1574\n#Imam Zulfiqar Ali, Khalilullah I, d. 1634\n#Imam Nur al-Din Ali, d. 1671\n#Imam Ali, Khalilullah II, d. 1680\n#Imam Nizar II, d. 1722\n#Imam Sayed Ali, d. ca. 1736\n#Imam Al-Hassan Ali Beg, d. ca. 1747\n#Imam Sayed Jafar, Al-Qasim Ali, d. ca. 1756\n#Imam Ab\u016b-l-Hasan \u02bbAl\u012b, d. 1792\n#Imam [[Shah Khalilullah III]], 1740\u20131817\n#Imam Hasan Ali Shah, [[Aga Khan I]], 1804\u20131881\n#Imam Aqa Ali Shah, [[Aga Khan II]], 1830\u20131885\n#Imam Sultan Muhammad Shah, [[Aga Khan III]], 1877\u20131957\n#Prince Sayyid [[Aly Khan]], 1911\u2013 1960\n#Imam Shah Karim Al-Hussaini, Aga Khan IV, b. 1936\n{{chart bottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links | wikt=no | b=no | n=no |s=no | v=no | voy=no | species=no |d=Q311793 | display=Aga Khan IV}}\n* [http://www.akdn.org/about_us/his-highness-aga-khan His Highness the Aga Khan]\n* [http://www.nanowisdoms.org NanoWisdoms Archive \u2013 Dedicated to the Aga Khan's speeches and interviews (over 600 readings and 1,000 quotes)]\n* [http://www.amaana.org/ismaili/imamat-day-july-11-2013/ His Highness the Aga Khan Spiritual Leader of Shia Ismailis]\n* [http://www.agakhanfilm.org An Islamic Conscience: the Aga Khan and the Ismailis \u2013 Film of HH the Aga Khan IV]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20111106113929/http://www.theismaili.org/cms/14/The-Aga-Khan About His Highness the Karim Aga Khan]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060520174934/http://www.princessinaara.org/ About Her Highness the Begum Aga Khan (PIF)]\n* [http://www.akdn.org/ Aga Khan Development Network]\n* [http://www.iis.ac.uk/ The Institute of Ismaili Studies]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080930190206/http://www.iis.ac.uk/view_article.asp?ContentID=103467 The Institute of Ismaili Studies: Introduction to His Highness the Aga Khan and Selected Speeches]\n* [http://www.sipa.columbia.edu/news_events/announcements/aga_khan.html Aga Khan article at SIPA (Columbia University)]\n* [http://www.brown.edu/Administration/News_Bureau/1995-96/95-147i.html Brown University President Vartan Gregorian's introduction of the Aga Khan (1996 baccalaureate address)]\n* [http://www.theismaili.org The Ismaili website]\n* [http://www.readthespirit.com/interfaith_heroes/2009/01/2nd-annual-interfaith-heroes-month-no-28-karim-alhussayni-aga-khan-iv-.html.html Read the spirit]{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n* [https://qz.com/1025313/a-rare-interview-with-the-aga-khan-on-poverty-climate-change-and-demistifying-islam/ A rare interview with the Aga Khan on poverty, climate change, and demystifying Islam] [[Quartz (publication)|''Quartz'']]\n* [https://ismailignosis.com/2015/08/02/the-secret-life-of-the-aga-khan/ The Secret Life of the Aga Khan]\n\n{{Agha Khan Fund for Economic Development}}\n{{Niz\u0101r\u012b}}\n{{Padma Vibhushan Awards|state=collapsed}}\n{{Agha Khans}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aga Khan 4}}\n[[Category:British imams]]\n[[Category:British philanthropists]]\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Aga Khan Development Network|.]]\n[[Category:British billionaires]]\n[[Category:British Ismailis]]\n[[Category:Nizari imams]]\n[[Category:Hashemite people]]\n[[Category:Fatimid dynasty]]\n[[Category:Qajar dynasty]]\n[[Category:Quran reciters]]\n[[Category:Commandeurs of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n[[Category:Commandeurs of the Ordre des Arts et des Lettres]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Institute of British Architects]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Institut Le Rosey]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:British people of Iranian descent]]\n[[Category:British people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:British people of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:British people of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:British expatriates in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:People from Geneva]]\n[[Category:Alpine skiers at the 1960 Winter 